text: Jakub Dyjas (born October 9, 1995) is a Polish table tennis player. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's singles event, in which he was eliminated in the second round by Alexander Shibaev, and as part of the Polish team in the men's team event. ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Polish male table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Poland Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:People from Koszalin Category:Table tennis players at the 2015 European Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Poland
